                              Refining

    Refining allows you to break down equipment to base materials. What
you receive after refining will depend on the material the equipment
is composed of. If the equipment isn't made of cloth, metals, or leathers,
it will not be refined. If you '|GKBrefine verbose|000' while in the refinery,
it will tell you the item name as well what was recovered. If you simply 
type '|GKBrefine|000' it will just list what was recovered.

    You may also use '|GKBset autorefine on|000' to automatically refine
eligible equipment from NPCs you kill. Automatic and manual refining use
the same material rules and yields. Autorefine is permanent and runs before
autoloot, so leave it off when you want to inspect equipment drops first.
Autorefine skips the same magical, unique, limited, customized, scripted,
and otherwise protected items that autosell refuses to sell; those stay in
the corpse for you to inspect or loot normally.
Autorefine and autosell cannot be enabled at the same time; enabling either
one disables the other. Autorefine does not require a corpse burner.

    The refinery is in the profession building, 4e, n from Center of Town.
Refining is a good way to turn unused equipment into saved profession
materials for crafting, work orders, recipe cards, and guildcraft.


    Most equipment that contains metal will break down to their base
metals. Leather equipment will always break down into Cow Leather. Cloth
equipment will always break down into Cotton Bolt(s). There is always
material loss while refining, so do not be surprised by that fact. If
you identify an object (using an identify scroll for example), you will
see if the object refines into anything, and what the result will be.
